<br>
    As a kitten I always wondered what that circle in the sky.  And as I grew older I was tired of guessing I wanted to know.    <br>
    From a young age I was taught in the ways of the mystiks, at the age of 20 I discovered a new from of magic not used by my people, the Veh'Shir.  The mystiks thought me a heretic when I showed them what I discovered, they banished me from the guild.  The magics I speak of are what your kind call wizardy, too advanced for my people to far behind for your people, I was forced to study on my own.  This thought drove me to become the best I could possible be, stronger and more knowledgeable than anyone else in the universe.  I quickly amassed power, surpassing even the eldest of shamans from my clan, or should I say my former clan.  I had all the knowledge that I could learn on this planet, it was time to learn more.  This is the beginning of my never ending quest.  I had to know what existed on Norrath as I began to call it.<br>
    I don't know where that name came from, I just woke up and couldn't put any other name on it.  After many years of research I discovered that it was a planet, that seemed to be inhabited by other creatures who possessed the powers of wizardry.  I must know what they know, I must surpass them, I must become the most powerful wizard, and I must get to that planet were the only thoughts that crossed my mind.  I spent many years researching and trying out different spells but none could get me to your planet.  <br>
     That is until I made a spell that transported me to a frozen wastes, all around me were creature I had only imagined seeing, now I knew where I was.  I was in the frozen wastes of Norrath.  <br>
     I did not know how I got here, and I did not know how to get back to my homeland.  Knowing my appearance would scare  the many races of Norrath I quickly made myself transparant.  I wandered for day before I found a single friendly creature, a bizarre scaled creature, double my height at least.  These creature were accepting of me, and told me of your kind.  Stories off the destruction you caused to their race, the merciless slayings of their family members.  This caused many questions to pop-up in my mind.  I was unsure wether to join these dragons, or to continue my quest to become the most powerful wizard anywhere.  Deciding to think about I followed these creature, dragons as you call them, around and noticed that they were killing your kind too.  My mind was made I was to continue my quest, I left them changed I learned many new spells that I had never tryed before, powerful spells.<br>
<br>
